14/20 Conversely when the MVRV STH is low it means that the market value of Bitcoin held by STH is close to or lower than the price at which they bought it.
13/20 When the MVRV STH is high it means that the market value of Bitcoin held by STH is much higher than the price at which they bought it. This could indicate a Distribution phase.
9/20 There are periods where the STH Realized Price is lower than the average Bitcoin price like early 2019 and early 2022. These periods could correspond to the Accumulation and Markdown phases.
8/20 The average purchase price of STH generally follows the trend of the average Bitcoin price indicating that STH's buying behavior is in line with the overall market trend.
7/20 But what are Short Term Holders (STH) doing during all of this? The red line on our graph represents the average price at which STH have bought their Bitcoin.
6/20 Markdown Phase: Characterized by falling prices and decreasing trading volume. Periods like late 2019 and late 2022 where the Bitcoin price is declining could be considered markdown phases.

5/20 Distribution Phase: Characterized by high prices and high trading volume. Periods like late 2021 could be distribution phases. Investors might be selling their Bitcoin to take profits or because they believe the price has peaked.
